title: Geriatric Psychiatry Organization Logo/website design
description: We are psychiatric medical providers who specialize in geriatric care. So our specialty and focus is memory care and treating mental health disorders in the elderly. We partner with assisted living facilities, skilled nursing facilities, rehab facilities, hospice companies etc. to come into their facility and see all of their patients monthly. We can also do this via telehealth. But we do not have a traditional outpatient clinic that we do this at. Our business model is to partner with these facilities to be part of their care team. We are board certified in psychiatry and have extensive experience working in geriatrics to properly diagnose and treat. Most of these facilities only have family doctors managing patients care, so we promote our expertise in sustaining healthier brains (to help provide the best quality of life as long as possible and prevent dementia) as the reason to have us also come in to see the patients at these homes. We are focused on the latest technology and treatments. And try to be as holistic as possible. We are focused on Idaho currently but hoping to expand to Oregon, Utah, Colorado, Montana and other states around Area in the future. It is possible we will expand over the years to other states across the country if the demand is there.
other_notes: I’m mostly interested in pictorial, abstract, mascot, combination and wordmark logos, but I’m open to all ideas. I would like the color palette to be inviting, modern and fun/playful to tie into our vision for our website. We want to depict joy and that youthfulness is still possible but also professional to speak to healthcare administrators who will be our primary person to establish contracts with. I don’t like logos which just have an animation on top and lettering underneath. I like when the artwork and lettering flow together and are more horizontal than vertical.
